'''Rrok Gjonlleshaj''' (born February 10, 1961 in Velež, [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]], today Velezha, [[Kosovo]]) is a [[Kosovo Albanians|Kosovo-Albanian]] clergyman and the current [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]] [[archbishop]] [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Bar|of Bar]].
==Life== After the end of his elementary studies in his native city, Rrok Gjonlleshaj studied [[philosophy]] and [[theology]] in [[Rijeka]] and received on 1 August 1987, the [[sacrament]] of [[Holy orders|Holy Orders]] for the [[Apostolic Administration of Prizren]]. He then worked in several [[parish]]es as a vicar and after as a pastor, most of them in [[Pristina]].<ref>[http://sq.radiovaticana.va/news/2016/04/05/meshtari_rrok_gjonlleshaj,_kryeipeshkvi_i_ri_i_tivarit/1220331 sq.radiovaticana.va]</ref> Gjonlleshaj was parish priest of the St. Anthony parish in Pristina as well as treasurer of the Apostolic Administration of Prizren. He was also the director of Radio Marija in [[Albanian language|Albanian]] and a contributor to the Drita religious-cultural show. On 5 April 2016 he was appointed by [[Pope Francis]] as Archbishop of Bar.<ref>[http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2016/04/05/0232/00509.html#ri press.vatican.va]</ref> His episcopal ordination was performed by his predecessor [[Zef Gashi]], [[Salesians of Don Bosco|SDB]] on 14 May of the same year and his Co- [[Consecration|consecrators]] were the [[Papal diplomacy|Apostolic Nuncio]] in [[Slovenia]], Archbishop [[Juliusz Janusz]], and the [[Apostolic Administrator]] of [[Apostolic Administration of Prizren|Prizren]], [[Dodë Gjergji]].
