{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2013}} {{Use South African English|date=January 2013}} {{Infobox serial killer |name=Stewart Wilken |image= |image_size= |caption= |birthname=Stewart Wilken |alias=Boetie Boer |birth_date={{birth date and age|1966|11|11}} |birth_place=[[Boksburg]], [[South Africa]] |death_date= |death_place= |cause= |victims=10+ |country=[[South Africa]] |states= |beginyear=1990 |endyear=1997 |apprehended=1997 |penalty=7 [[life sentence]]s }}
'''Stewart Wilken''' AKA "Boetie Boer" (born 11 November 1966) is a convicted serial killer from [[South Africa]]. Wilken is regarded as a highly unusual serial killer, having killed individuals from two distinct victim types: female prostitutes and young boys (he also killed his adolescent daughter, Wuane). Wilken killed from 1990 until he was arrested in January 1997. He was active in [[Port Elizabeth]], on the east coast of South Africa.<ref name="A">{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oN_QKBYvSloC&pg=PA344 | title=Serial Murderers and their Victims | publisher=Cengage Learning | pages=344– | isbn=9784956008143}}</ref><ref name="Pistorius2002">{{cite book|last=Pistorius|first=Micki | authorlink = Micki Pistorius |title=Strangers on the street: serial homicide in South Africa|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=s7cEAQAAIAAJ|accessdate=5 April 2012|year=2002|publisher=Penguin|isbn=9780141003566}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/local-news/north-harbour-news/696177|title=Story of a serial killer|date=30 October 2008|work=North Harbour News|accessdate=5 April 2012}}</ref>
Wilken was charged with 10 counts of murder and 5 counts of sodomy on 3 February 1997. He was convicted of 7 counts of murder and 2 counts of sodomy on 20 February 1998. Wilken received seven life sentences and was further advised by Justice Chris Jansen that he would have received the death penalty had it still been available to him.
He killed his daughter, Wuane, who was born from his first marriage. He said that she was sexually abused by her step-dad and wanted to send her soul to God. He killed Henry Bakers, the son of his second wife. He said during an interview with the police that he had sex with Henry's decomposing corpse. He also stated that he ate the nipples of one of his victims.<ref name="A"/>
